search:Kafka Integration and Performance.content:
- Install Confluent.Kafka NuGet package using `dotnet add package Confluent.Kafka`
- Use latest version of Confluent.Kafka, as of my last update it's 2.0.0.
- Key config options for producer: `BootstrapServers`, `ClientId`, `SecurityProtocol`, `SslCaLocation` (if using SSL).
- Key config options for consumer: `BootstrapServers`, `GroupId`, `AutoOffsetReset`, `EnableAutoCommit`.
- Example of creating a Kafka producer:
  ```csharp
  var conf = new ProducerConfig { BootstrapServers = "localhost:9092" };
  using (var p = new ProducerBuilder<Null, string>(conf).Build())
  {
      try
      {
          var dr = await p.ProduceAsync("my-topic", new Message<Null, string> { Value = "Hello World!" });
          Console.WriteLine($"Delivered message to {dr.TopicPartitionOffset}");
      }
      catch (KafkaException e)
      {
          Console.WriteLine($"Delivery failed: {e.Error.Reason}");
      }
  }
  ```
- Example of creating a Kafka consumer:
  ```csharp
  var conf = new ConsumerConfig
  {
      BootstrapServers = "localhost:9092",
      GroupId = "my-group",
      AutoOffsetReset = AutoOffsetReset.Earliest,
      EnableAutoCommit = true
  };
  using (var c = new ConsumerBuilder<Ignore, string>(conf).Build())
  {
      c.Subscribe("my-topic");
      try
      {
          while (true)
          {
              var cr = c.Consume();
              Console.WriteLine($"Consumed message '{cr.Value}' at: '{cr.TopicPartitionOffset}'.");
          }
      }
      catch (ConsumeException e)
      {
          Console.WriteLine($"Error occured: {e.Error.Reason}");
      }
  }
  ```
